import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax, label='Temperature Max')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, ax=ax, label='Temperature Min')
    plt.title('How do temperature max and temperature min vary over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data['weekday'] = data['date'].dt.weekday
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].str.title()
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=weather_counts.index, y=weather_counts.values, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of weather in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    for i, v in enumerate(weather_counts.values):
        plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontweight='bold')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
